WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:05.600
The following programme contains
strong language and violent scenes.

2
00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:32.239
I got you a present. Elly.

3
00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:33.519
It's Elly.

4
00:00:48.600 --> 00:00:51.999
Sean's dead. Billy.
Two guys brought the body to Luan.

5
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.439
He did it. He killed my daughter.

6
00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:56.199
With Billy and Cornelius.

7
00:00:56.200 --> 00:00:57.959
His name is Elliot Carter.

8
00:00:57.960 --> 00:01:00.399
I want this guy
to be our number-one target.

9
00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:02.799
We find the evidence
and lock him the fuck up.

10
00:01:02.800 --> 00:01:04.359
Evening. fellas.

11
00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:06.400
Yeah? Whoa!

12
00:01:07.320 --> 00:01:09.319
They tell me that firearm possession

13
00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:11.679
is a good ten years.
I'm not the one you're looking for.

14
00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:15.279
'You find that clean cocaine.
you find the people that did this.'

15
00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:16.800
We can help each other.

16
00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:19.919
Oh. my God.

17
00:01:19.920 --> 00:01:23.919
You've had your pound of flesh.
Let it go. Luan. It's done.

18
00:01:23.920 --> 00:01:25.799
You don't want a war. None of us do.

19
00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:29.479
Luan thinks you're to blame
for his daughter's death

20
00:01:29.480 --> 00:01:31.119
and he wants you dead.

21
00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:32.759
I can offer you protection.

22
00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:36.039
But I want you to help me
destroy those who murdered Sean.

23
00:04:04.240 --> 00:04:05.639
Luan.

24
00:04:05.640 --> 00:04:07.080
Luan!

25
00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:50.440
Mind your heads.
Mind your heads.

26
00:05:14.120 --> 00:05:17.000
The funeral is for family only.

27
00:05:20.960 --> 00:05:24.800
There are rumours that Billy
and Cornelius are planning to attend.

28
00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:30.200
I don't think that that's -
I've told them to keep away.

29
00:05:31.200 --> 00:05:33.200
I don't want any trouble.

30
00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:36.159
Not today. anyway.

31
00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:37.960
And tomorrow?

32
00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:48.719
I know what it is
to bury a son. Marian.

33
00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:53.800
Please do not confuse your grief
with a need for revenge.

34
00:07:17.200 --> 00:07:19.159
I'm going to walk.

35
00:08:24.560 --> 00:08:26.520
It's not really funeral attire.
is it?

36
00:08:27.560 --> 00:08:30.040
Aren't they burying your mate today?

37
00:08:32.360 --> 00:08:35.039
What've you got for me?
A random spot check

38
00:08:35.040 --> 00:08:38.039
pulled over a transit van headed
out of the city the other morning.

39
00:08:38.040 --> 00:08:39.759
One of many. of course. but um...

40
00:08:39.760 --> 00:08:41.839
didn't know what we were looking
for at the time.

41
00:08:41.840 --> 00:08:43.919
After your tip-off
we went over the logs

42
00:08:43.920 --> 00:08:46.440
and saw it had a cargo
full of beer kegs.

43
00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:52.359
This one. Turns out
the plates didn't match the vehicle.

44
00:08:52.360 --> 00:08:54.839
Did they ID the driver?
Well. yeah.

45
00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:56.919
but I'm sure you can guess.

46
00:08:56.920 --> 00:08:58.839
Also fake? Mm-hm.

47
00:08:58.840 --> 00:09:00.839
We know it was a woman. that's it.

48
00:09:00.840 --> 00:09:03.720
Now. traffic cameras pick her
up near this garage.

49
00:09:04.840 --> 00:09:06.479
Then nothing.

50
00:09:06.480 --> 00:09:10.079
The guy who runs the place
has a pretty questionable past.

51
00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:13.280
The assumption is she's changed
the plates again. but er...

52
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:17.240
he's not the type to talk to the
police. which is a... shame.

53
00:09:18.960 --> 00:09:22.719
Because if there was someone
who could get him to... open up...

54
00:09:22.720 --> 00:09:24.760
give us the new registration...

55
00:09:25.760 --> 00:09:28.400
Then you could track the plates.
Mm.

56
00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:31.960
Alright. Elliot...

57
00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:35.400
I'm trusting
you know where the line is.

58
00:09:36.400 --> 00:09:39.040
Mine. right? Not yours.

59
00:09:40.800 --> 00:09:43.120
Someone crossed that line
a long time ago.

60
00:09:45.160 --> 00:09:47.799
I don't want blood on my hands.
We may have a deal

61
00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:50.239
but I don't work for you.

62
00:09:50.240 --> 00:09:52.400
So you draw your lines.
I'll draw mine.

63
00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:56.680
You know. you have less than a week
to deliver me results. Elliot.

64
00:09:57.960 --> 00:09:59.760
Remember that.

65
00:10:22.720 --> 00:10:24.639
Lale!

66
00:10:45.960 --> 00:10:47.320
Lale.

67
00:11:05.000 --> 00:11:06.200
Lale.

68
00:11:19.400 --> 00:11:20.880
Yes?

69
00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:26.999
You said this wouldn't be a problem.

70
00:12:35.600 --> 00:12:37.400
Mrs Wallace.

71
00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:42.600
Um... I'm sorry for your loss.

72
00:12:44.680 --> 00:12:46.439
Do I know you?

73
00:12:46.440 --> 00:12:48.360
I knew Sean.

74
00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:56.440
It wasn't right.
what happened to him.

75
00:12:58.080 --> 00:13:02.360
This is a private service.
family only.

76
00:13:06.040 --> 00:13:07.520
Of course.

77
00:14:54.840 --> 00:14:57.639
What the fuck are you doing here?
It's supposed to be Saba and Faz.

78
00:14:57.640 --> 00:15:00.279
It's not just you who's fucked
if we don't get that stock back.

79
00:15:00.280 --> 00:15:03.599
Yeah. I know but -So why are you
running around on your own?

80
00:15:03.600 --> 00:15:07.639
We're meant to be partners in this.
Listen. there's a man in there

81
00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:09.680
who I need to get talking and...

82
00:15:10.600 --> 00:15:12.479
it might get messy.

83
00:15:12.480 --> 00:15:13.880
And?

84
00:15:17.360 --> 00:15:19.359
So who gave you your lead?

85
00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:21.999
An old friend from the force.
He owed me one.

86
00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:23.639
Seriously?

87
00:15:23.640 --> 00:15:26.440
- You better be sure.
- You can trust him. - I am.

88
00:15:27.640 --> 00:15:29.640
Excuse me. are you the owner?

89
00:15:30.320 --> 00:15:32.400
Depends who's asking.

90
00:15:36.160 --> 00:15:38.119
Transit came in here two nights ago.

91
00:15:38.120 --> 00:15:41.639
Registration CK61 WKN.

92
00:15:41.640 --> 00:15:44.599
You changed the plates.
You lot deaf or fucking stupid?

93
00:15:44.600 --> 00:15:47.599
- Said already. I don't know nothing.
- About it. - We're not the police.

94
00:15:47.600 --> 00:15:51.000
Either way. I don't give a fuck.
love. Ain't seen no transit van.

95
00:16:32.920 --> 00:16:34.160
Ready.

96
00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:56.680
What the fuck is this?

97
00:16:57.880 --> 00:16:59.319
Where is everyone?

98
00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:03.759
It's a trap.

99
00:17:30.640 --> 00:17:32.559
No. no. no. no. no. no!

100
00:17:32.560 --> 00:17:34.520
Luan!

101
00:18:07.720 --> 00:18:09.680
Go. go. go. go. go!

102
00:18:42.040 --> 00:18:44.400
Argh!

103
00:19:15.480 --> 00:19:17.160
Argh!

104
00:19:29.480 --> 00:19:30.760
Arghhh!

105
00:20:50.800 --> 00:20:52.519
Arh!

106
00:21:04.160 --> 00:21:05.360
Stay back.

107
00:21:06.240 --> 00:21:08.240
Stay the fuck back.

108
00:21:09.240 --> 00:21:11.600
I'm gonna fucking kill her. Yeah?

109
00:21:18.800 --> 00:21:20.079
Shoot him. Billy.

110
00:21:20.080 --> 00:21:22.199
No. No. they don't.

111
00:21:22.200 --> 00:21:24.439
Yeah.

112
00:21:24.440 --> 00:21:26.759
Cos Mama gonna die. Come on.

113
00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:28.880
I said stay back!

114
00:21:35.800 --> 00:21:37.120
Stay back. Billy.

115
00:21:45.160 --> 00:21:49.520
Put the gun down
or I'll fucking kill her.

116
00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:52.520
And do it now.

117
00:21:53.360 --> 00:21:54.999
Now!

118
00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:57.040
Do as he says. lad.

119
00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:02.999
Billy. put the fucking gun down

120
00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:05.359
or you'll be burying
two Wallaces today.

121
00:22:05.360 --> 00:22:07.999
This is the last fucking warning!

122
00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:11.120
Billy.
Listen to your fucking uncle. Billy.

123
00:22:12.280 --> 00:22:13.960
Fuck you!

124
00:22:14.840 --> 00:22:16.840
Fucking kill him. Billy!

125
00:22:50.120 --> 00:22:51.600
What the fuck?

126
00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:55.160
Who was driving the van?

127
00:22:58.880 --> 00:23:00.840
Fuck you.

128
00:23:06.640 --> 00:23:08.799
Try again. Who was driving the van?

129
00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:12.439
I didn't see anyone. The van
was just here in the morning.

130
00:23:12.440 --> 00:23:15.159
I did the job and they picked it up
after I'd gone home.

131
00:23:15.160 --> 00:23:17.399
Who asked you to do the job?
I get calls.

132
00:23:17.400 --> 00:23:19.159
I don't ask fucking questions.

133
00:23:21.640 --> 00:23:24.320
I would tell you. I would.

134
00:23:25.400 --> 00:23:27.640
You... Fuck!

135
00:23:32.600 --> 00:23:36.840
- You want the new reg. yeah?
- Mm-hm. Have it. It's over there in my desk.

136
00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:39.639
I want a name.

137
00:23:39.640 --> 00:23:42.480
Don't look at her. Look at me.

138
00:23:43.760 --> 00:23:45.439
I don't have a fucking name.

139
00:23:45.440 --> 00:23:47.839
No! No! Don't! Please!

140
00:23:50.600 --> 00:23:53.040
Please! Oh. fuck!

141
00:23:53.760 --> 00:23:56.519
I don't... I don't... You don't...
I don't know! Please!

142
00:23:56.520 --> 00:23:59.119
Elliot. Elliot. Stop!

143
00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:02.599
This is a waste of time.
Let's just get the plate number.

144
00:24:02.600 --> 00:24:03.800
Go on.

145
00:24:08.240 --> 00:24:12.159
Yeah. Arghhh!

146
00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:14.040
Fuck!

147
00:24:23.200 --> 00:24:26.159
- Elliot?
- Don't fucking do that. What the fuck was that about?

148
00:24:26.160 --> 00:24:29.519
What difference would a name make?
We know Sean was behind this.

149
00:24:29.520 --> 00:24:31.560
Yeah. well. I think he was set up.

150
00:24:32.560 --> 00:24:34.119
So what now?

151
00:24:34.120 --> 00:24:36.239
Well. I'll run the new reg
with my friend -

152
00:24:36.240 --> 00:24:39.160
assuming you don't have a problem
with me using them again.

153
00:24:47.160 --> 00:24:51.039
You mix a sample of whatever drug
you're planning to take with water.

154
00:24:51.040 --> 00:24:54.559
dip the paper strip in
and if any fentanyl is detected

155
00:24:54.560 --> 00:24:56.439
a single line will appear.

156
00:24:56.440 --> 00:24:58.759
Um... how soon can we roll this out?

157
00:24:58.760 --> 00:25:01.959
People are dying every day from
this contaminated cocaine batch.

158
00:25:01.960 --> 00:25:03.879
Well. we're working quickly.

159
00:25:03.880 --> 00:25:07.039
- 24 hours?
- Do you know how we're gonna spin this?

160
00:25:07.040 --> 00:25:09.799
The public
haven't exactly been receptive

161
00:25:09.800 --> 00:25:12.559
to policies they see
as enabling drug use in the past.

162
00:25:12.560 --> 00:25:14.799
Our polling
suggests the tide is turning.

163
00:25:14.800 --> 00:25:17.199
People want these deaths to stop.

164
00:25:17.200 --> 00:25:18.840
Oh... er...

165
00:25:21.480 --> 00:25:25.400
I'm sorry er... can you excuse me?
Something urgent's come up.

166
00:25:26.560 --> 00:25:27.919
Er... you need me?

167
00:25:27.920 --> 00:25:30.880
Er... no. no. You stay.
You can fill me in later.

168
00:25:55.080 --> 00:25:57.080
Mirlinda?

169
00:25:58.760 --> 00:26:00.199
Mirlinda!

170
00:26:17.560 --> 00:26:20.319
Shit. OK. OK.

171
00:26:20.320 --> 00:26:21.839
Wait.

172
00:26:24.640 --> 00:26:27.320
- Shit. shit. shit.
- Alright. - OK.

173
00:26:28.280 --> 00:26:29.640
Er... Bukuroshe.

174
00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:46.320
Luan.

175
00:26:58.600 --> 00:26:59.960
Luan?

176
00:27:56.200 --> 00:27:58.200
Luan wants to make a deal.

177
00:28:00.040 --> 00:28:04.559
Luan is willing to give you anything
you want as an act of contrition.

178
00:28:04.560 --> 00:28:06.639
Businesses. routes.

179
00:28:06.640 --> 00:28:09.799
Everything you need
he'll hand over to you.

180
00:28:09.800 --> 00:28:12.319
He will not seek any more revenge

181
00:28:12.320 --> 00:28:14.320
as long as you agree to the same.

182
00:28:15.240 --> 00:28:17.000
How magnanimous We can work -

183
00:29:12.920 --> 00:29:14.919
He's gone. Fuck!

184
00:29:14.920 --> 00:29:16.839
They can't have got far.

185
00:29:16.840 --> 00:29:18.640
Find them.

186
00:30:00.120 --> 00:30:01.640
This is the place.

187
00:30:02.440 --> 00:30:05.000
Traffic cameras
picked up the van driving in here.

188
00:30:13.920 --> 00:30:15.440
Give me a minute.

189
00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:09.919
Check those plates.

190
00:31:09.920 --> 00:31:11.720
Anything? No.

191
00:31:40.880 --> 00:31:42.440
Hey!

192
00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:27.520
Did you see the driver? No.

193
00:32:42.520 --> 00:32:44.520
Yeah. OK. thanks. Dad.

194
00:32:45.400 --> 00:32:48.479
Dad's gonna get Faz and Saba
and the others looking for that van.

195
00:32:48.480 --> 00:32:50.519
We were so close.

196
00:32:50.520 --> 00:32:52.200
Hey. hey. hey.

197
00:32:54.440 --> 00:32:56.680
What aren't you telling me?

198
00:32:57.960 --> 00:32:59.400
Elliot.

199
00:33:00.400 --> 00:33:02.480
What the fuck?

200
00:33:03.960 --> 00:33:05.959
That logo.

201
00:33:05.960 --> 00:33:07.760
I've seen it before.

202
00:33:13.400 --> 00:33:16.080
It was on some files Naomi had.

203
00:33:17.120 --> 00:33:18.840
Naomi as in your wife?

204
00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:23.320
Look. the guy who took Sean...

205
00:33:24.440 --> 00:33:28.240
I recognised him cos he's also the
driver who killed Naomi and Samuel.

206
00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:31.560
Are you sure?

207
00:33:35.000 --> 00:33:37.919
The spiking. the hit-and-run.

208
00:33:37.920 --> 00:33:39.920
What if it's all connected?

209
00:33:40.720 --> 00:33:44.719
Maybe she was investigating them
and that's why they had her killed.

210
00:33:44.720 --> 00:33:48.319
- Sean said the driver was paid to run.
- Her off the road. - Hang on a minute.

211
00:33:48.320 --> 00:33:50.360
This is all coming from Sean?

212
00:33:52.040 --> 00:33:53.839
Elliot.

213
00:33:53.840 --> 00:33:56.080
Sean knew how much
this would hurt you.

214
00:33:56.960 --> 00:33:58.720
He wanted you chasing ghosts.

215
00:34:01.600 --> 00:34:04.600
I still have some of
Naomi's things at Dad's.

216
00:34:05.680 --> 00:34:07.920
Maybe there's something in there.
Yeah.

217
00:34:15.400 --> 00:34:17.279
Look. why don't I come with you?

218
00:34:17.280 --> 00:34:18.600
No.

219
00:34:20.560 --> 00:34:21.799
Thank you.

220
00:34:21.800 --> 00:34:25.480
Yeah. no. it's fine. I'll um...
I'll look into that logo.

221
00:35:23.040 --> 00:35:25.680
Nothing yet. They've gone to ground.

222
00:35:26.560 --> 00:35:30.199
It's just a matter of time. We're searching
every business they're connected to.

223
00:35:30.200 --> 00:35:32.239
every safe house and every port.

224
00:35:32.240 --> 00:35:33.920
I'll find them.

225
00:35:59.200 --> 00:36:01.280
Er... one minute.

226
00:36:02.280 --> 00:36:04.400
Shit.

227
00:36:09.120 --> 00:36:11.160
OK!

228
00:36:15.760 --> 00:36:17.719
Problem?

229
00:36:17.720 --> 00:36:19.400
You tell me.

230
00:36:20.280 --> 00:36:22.359
What. I don't know what you mean?
Um...

231
00:36:22.360 --> 00:36:25.479
well. disappearing
during office hours.

232
00:36:25.480 --> 00:36:27.599
mysterious messages.

233
00:36:27.600 --> 00:36:31.560
When you are here.
you seem er... distracted.

234
00:36:32.280 --> 00:36:34.360
Spit it out. Henry.
what are you getting at?

235
00:36:35.520 --> 00:36:38.320
Are you using again? Er...

236
00:36:39.320 --> 00:36:41.400
I am...

237
00:36:42.840 --> 00:36:44.759
I'm working with Elliot Carter.

238
00:36:44.760 --> 00:36:47.199
He says he was set up
with contaminated cocaine.

239
00:36:47.200 --> 00:36:50.079
That someone
swapped his clean product

240
00:36:50.080 --> 00:36:52.120
with a batch that had been spiked.

241
00:36:52.800 --> 00:36:55.119
And you believe him?
I'm simply giving him

242
00:36:55.120 --> 00:36:56.959
the opportunity to prove it.

243
00:36:56.960 --> 00:36:58.839
Have you lost your fucking mind?

244
00:36:58.840 --> 00:37:01.239
Tell me you didn't
get him out of custody.

245
00:37:01.240 --> 00:37:05.679
Elliot has made more progress in one
day. than the police have all week.

246
00:37:05.680 --> 00:37:08.959
Look. he's currently tracking
the van the drugs were smuggled in.

247
00:37:08.960 --> 00:37:12.079
Colluding with the criminals we're
supposed to be fighting against

248
00:37:12.080 --> 00:37:15.439
is not the way to win this.
OK. then tell me what is. Henry?

249
00:37:15.440 --> 00:37:17.479
Because right now. no-one believes

250
00:37:17.480 --> 00:37:20.159
that we can actually do anything
about these gangs.

251
00:37:20.160 --> 00:37:23.239
I'm just another politician
spouting a load of shit.

252
00:37:23.240 --> 00:37:25.480
making empty promises.

253
00:37:27.480 --> 00:37:29.480
Legalisation of all drugs.

254
00:37:30.320 --> 00:37:32.919
It's your policy.
You said it yourself.

255
00:37:32.920 --> 00:37:35.999
It's the only way
to hit all the gangs at once -

256
00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:37.639
take away their business.

257
00:37:37.640 --> 00:37:40.479
Yes. and I dropped it
from the campaign for a reason.

258
00:37:40.480 --> 00:37:43.719
There just isn't enough support.
Yes. but that was before

259
00:37:43.720 --> 00:37:47.200
hundreds of people died in
a single night from poisoned drugs.

